 :tx/rationale "Create task: DAEMON-2: Protocol layer — JSON-lines over Unix domain socket (INV-INTERFACE-008, FD-012). BACKGROUND: The daemon serves CLI commands via a Unix domain socket at .braid/braid.sock. Need a simple, debuggable wire protocol. APPROACH: (1) Request format: {\"cmd\": \"status\", \"args\": {\"verbose\": false, ...}, \"id\": \"req-001\"}. One JSON object per line. (2) Response format: {\"id\": \"req-001\", \"ok\": true, \"result\": {\"json\": ..., \"human\": \"...\", \"agent\": {...}}}. Error: {\"id\": \"req-001\", \"ok\": false, \"error\": \"message\"}. (3) Use tokio::net::UnixListener for async socket handling. Single-threaded tokio runtime (the store is not Send — no need for multi-thread). (4) Each connection handles one request-response then closes (HTTP/1.0 style). This avoids connection state management. (5) Timeout: 120s per request (matches CLI timeout). (6) Socket permissions: 0600 (owner only). ACCEPTANCE: (A) Daemon listens on .braid/braid.sock. (B) CLI can send JSON request and receive JSON response. (C) Response matches CommandOutput format (json + human + agent fields). (D) Error responses include diagnostic message. (E) Socket cleaned up on daemon exit. (F) Permission 0600. DEPENDS-ON: DAEMON-1 (t-0a1b5c4e). FILE: crates/braid/src/daemon.rs (new)"
